The paper deals with feature acquisition and learning performance, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of matrix completion and active feature querying also suggests a focus on optimization and data analysis, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The mention of correlation between features and cost-aware active selection also suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
